Vice President Mike Pence has arrived in Japan to meet with foreign leaders and discuss security on the Korean Peninsula. He will also lead the U.S. Delegation to the 2018 Olympic Winter Games in Pyeongchang. Before arriving in Japan, Pence stopped in Alaska to review America's missile defense capabilities. During his visit, he will reaffirm the United States' commitment to its allies and show support for U.S. athletes and military stationed in the region. This is Pence's second visit to Japan and South Korea in less than a year.